analysis: The documents all pertain to the establishment or expansion of wildlife refuges, primarily for migratory birds, under the authority of the President of the United States. They specify the land being set aside, often with detailed geographical descriptions, and prohibit activities like hunting or disturbing wildlife within the refuge boundaries. The documents reflect a conservation effort to protect bird populations and other wildlife by creating protected habitats.
title: Establishment and Expansion of Wildlife Refuges for Migratory Birds
